As exclusive marketing agents, CBRE are pleased to present to the market for the first time – the opportunity to acquire the freehold ownership to a truly iconic piece of real estate in one of Sydney’s most affluent inner city suburbs.

Located atop the Drummoyne Peninsula, the Drummoyne Reservoir otherwise known as lots 13, 14, 15 and 16 of deposited plan 455626 offers astute developers and investors an unique island site with existing improvements suitable for reconfiguration or adaptive redevelopment (STCA).

Key features of the property includes; 

- Combined land area of 1,802sqm*on an island site with four street frontages
- Most unique opportunity offered in one of Sydney’s most affluent inner city locations only 6kms* from Sydney CBD
- Potential for residential, commercial, community or mixed use adaptive redevelopment (STCA)
- Decommissioned heritage water reservoir with an endorsed Conservation Management Plan in place
- Comprehensive due-diligence support for reconfiguration or re-adaption use
- Situated on the high-point of the Drummoyne Peninsula with unhindered 360° view from the current improvements
- Great accessibility to major amenity and employment hubs via Victoria Road and Lyons Road


For a copy of the Information Memorandum or to find out more about the property, please contact the exclusive marketing agents at CBRE.

*approx

CBRE and Savills are pleased to present Rowland House and Marlborough House, 4 Stuart Street, Drummoyne. 

The subject site consists of two apartment blocks across one title which are well positioned to capitalise on the burgeoning Inner West property market. The property has DA Approval for 17 luxury apartments whilst the site’s current improvements provide prospective buyers with further value-add potential through refurbishment and strata subdivision (STCA).

Rowland House and Marlborough House benefits from the following key attributes:

- Two existing apartment blocks
- A total of 22 x 1 bedroom units
- DA Approved for 17 luxury apartments with a combined NSA of 1,989sqm*
- Total land area: 1,775sqm*
- Significant refurbishment and strata subdivision potential
- Offered with vacant possession – Ready for construction or refurbishment
- Bus and Ferry options with direct access to Sydney CBD
- Situated within close proximity to the future Bays Precinct and Sydney West Metro network
- Only 400m* from Drummoyne Town Centre

The property will be sold via an expressions of interest campaign closing on Wednesday, 11th March 2020 at 4.00pm.
